  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Recovery of Colombian Indigenous Territory through Specialty Cocoa Production</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will focus on improving the economic livelihoods of members of the Tairuna indigenous community through the production of quality cacao. The primary project objectives are:  Establishment of new production sites of special aromatic cocoa in talanqueras populations, Strengthen management of new production sites through inclusion of organic cultivation practices, Polyculture model integrated to the production of special cocoa, Supporting the artisanal activity of indigenous women in the talanqueras populations as part of their livelihoods, Integration of environmentally sustainable irrigation systems</narrative>
  </description>
